               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18441021-name-1109" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18441021-name-1109" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18441021-name-1109" type="surname" value="BIGG"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18441021-name-1109" type="given" value="MARY ANN"></interp>MARY ANN BIGG</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of Edward Bigg—we live in Westmore<lb></lb>land-place, land-place, Camberwell. On the 18th of <hi rend="italic">Oct</hi>. we had a time-piece—I saw it safe at half-past seven o'clock that morning—I missed it at ten minutes past eight—this is it—I had left the parlour window open a little way—there were flower-pots outside.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. ROBINSON</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Are you quite sure you saw it safe at half-past seven? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18441021-name-1110" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18441021-name-1110" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18441021-name-1110" type="surname" value="ROBINS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18441021-name-1110" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>EDWARD ROBINS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a gardener. On Friday morning, the 18th of Oct., I saw the two prisoners walking about Westmoreland-place—I watched them, and saw Randall go into the prosecutor's window, and take out the time-piece, and deliver it to Ashley—I and Clark ran after them—Clark caught Ashley, and I ran and took Randall.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Did Ashley run away? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> He could not—he was held tight by Clark, and I ran after Randall—I saw some flower-pots taken down by one of the prisoners, I do not know which, and Randall got in at the window—that I swear—it was about ten minutes past eight—the pri<lb></lb>soners were together—I saw them together—while Randall went in Ashley was outside, on the grass-plot in the little garden—I have known both the prisoners for some time.</p>
